Former Champion Maria Sharapova Upset by Flavia Pennetta at US Open Tennis

-- B y   R o b   G l o s t e r
-- 
2011-09-02T20:16:20Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-02/former-champion-maria-sharapova-upset-by-flavia-pennetta-at-us-open-tennis.html
Former champion  Maria Sharapova  of
 Russia  was defeated in the third round at the U.S. Open today,
losing in three sets to Flavia Pennetta of Italy.  Sharapova, 24, who won the title in 2006 and is the third
seed this year, made 60 unforced errors while losing 6-3, 3-6,
6-4. She had 12 double faults and no aces in the match.  Sharapova is the highest seed, man or woman, to lose so far
at this yearâ€™s Open.  Pennetta, 29, the 26th seed, is a two-time U.S. Open
quarterfinalist.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
